name: Kampung Coklat jembrana
address: Pohsanten, Mendoyo, Jembrana Regency, Bali 82261, Indonesia
review 1: very nice and well-kept grounds.  The road to this place is already very beautiful.  The people are friendly and the chocolate is tasty.  We've only been there a short time.
review 2:
when i visit the gate was closed eventhough there is a security man there but no one open the gate until i get out from my car walk to them and asking if they are open or not.
arrive at the parking area i went to the toilet but it has many mosquito and dirty, they have a bakery but not bake anything, at that place you just can buy cocoa powder but only that suit the name kampung coklat (cocoa village), way to the restaurant i pass a pool full of death fish,on my way to the restaurant the gardener put down his lawn mower  right on the path. the toilet at the restaurant extreemely dirty even the toilet at the petrol statiom near there is much much better.

there is no food at the restaurant that you can order, drink only, no food ready even though there is a food and beverage menu there.

the tast of their chocolate drink is so so, much watter, less chocolate, rich of sugar.

the plus point only the waitrees is helpful, just it.
review 3: still under construction but overall will be one of the best campground and local chocolate education place in west bali
